item.title: US-395 North - WA-17 Interchange
item.description: US-395 North at WA-17 North to Mesa and Moses Lake.

item.title: US-2 West/WA-17 North Approaching US-2/WA-17 Split
item.description: US-2 West/WA-17 North approaching US-2/WA-17 split in Douglas County. Use WA-17 north for Bridgeport and Chief Joseph Dam.

item.title: WA-17 North at US-2 - Dry Falls Junction
item.description: WA-17 North at US-2. Turn right for US-2 East/To WA-155/Grand Coulee Dam/Spokane. Turn left for US-2 West/WA-17 North/Wenatchee. WA-17 north joins US-2 westbound for about 2 miles.

item.title: WA-17 North Approaching US-2
item.description: WA-17 North approaching US-2 to Spokane and Wenatchee.

item.title: WA-28 West at WA-17 - Soap Lake
item.description: WA-28 West at WA-17 junction in Soap Lake. Turn left for WA-17 south to Moses Lake; right for WA-17 north to Soap Lake (City Center).

item.title: WA-28 West Approaching WA-17
item.description: WA-28 West approaching WA-17 to Soap Lake and Moses Lake.

item.title: End WA-17 South at US-395
item.description: End WA-17 South at US-395 in Franklin County. Use US-395 south for Pasco; US-395 north for Spokane.

item.title: WA-17 South Approaching WA-260
item.description: WA-17 south approaching WA-260 east to Connell and Washtucna.

item.title: WA-17 South at WA-26
item.description: WA-17 south at WA-26 in Adams County. Use WA-26 for WA-24/Yakima/Pullman. Continue south on WA-17 for US-395/Pasco.

item.title: WA-17 South Approaching WA-174
item.description: WA-17 south approaching WA-174 East to Grand Coulee Dam. Continue south on WA-17 for Coulee City and Moses Lake.

item.title: WA-17 South Approaching WA-173 North
item.description: WA-17 south approaching WA-173 North/Bridgeport/Brewster. Crossing the Columbia River into Douglas County.

item.title: US-97 South Approaching WA-17
item.description: US-97 south approaching WA-17 South to Bridgeport and Moses Lake.
